The Civil Protection reports numerous criticalities on the territory of the Metropolitan City of&nbsp; Firenze, in particular because of floods due to the abundant rains that are affecting the minor lattice and the sewer system, landslides and fall of trees.> The main criticisms are the closure of the provincial road 41 in the locality Ponte a Vicchio for flooding, and the&nbsp; Firenze-Siena in San Casciano Val di Pesa, in direction&nbsp; Firenze, for fall of trees.&nbsp;
Prato is also struggling with flooding and fallen trees.> In particular, inconvenience to the circulation in Galilei Avenue, at the height of the Datini bridge, for the fall of a large pine on the road: firefighters are underway to remove the tree. Enlarged via del Leone in San Giorgio a Colonica: the road has been closed at the height of via del Salciolo because not accessible. Problems on all the lattice of roads between Donald, Castelnuovo and San Giorgio where the lateral pits are at the limit of tracimation. Also close to Figline due to flooding and removal. Closed precautionally via di Cantagallo from the roundabout with Via VII Marzo to the roundabout with via Malcantone and Vignone. On the night the closing of Via Valdingole and Fossetto was arranged where the underpass was flooded.
In high Tuscany, a landfall on the regional road 445 of Garfagnana between Ponte di Calavorno and Ponte della Fegana> which, added to the interruption of the highway 12 of Brennero for works, has determined the substantial isolation of Bagni di Lucca. The situation in the morning was made even more critical because the municipal road of Corsagna is congested and affected by an accident that occurred between two vehicles. Those from Bagni di Lucca must head towards Barga or Castelnuovo di Garfagnana must use the provincial road 56 and transit from the localities Tereglio-Vitiana. No transit to heavy goods vehicles. The mayor of Borgo a Mozzano, Patrizio Andreuccetti, informs that Anas was asked to reopen the Ss 12 for the passage of the means of aid (the possibility of reopening temporarily also to normal pathability is under evaluation). Due to the bad weather there are delays on the Lucca-Aulla railway.

